This article is a press briefing from the White House on President Obama's upcoming trip to Guadalajara. The briefing includes statements from National Security Advisor General James Jones, Deputy National Security Advisor for International Economic Affairs Michael Froman, NSC Senior Director of Western Hemisphere Affairs Daniel Restrepo, and Deputy National Security Advisor for Counterterrorism and Homeland Security John Brennan. The briefing discusses the importance of the President's trip to Mexico, the North American Leaders Summit, and the topics that will be discussed, including the global economy, energy, climate change, and security. The briefing also touches on the H1N1 flu virus and the ongoing cooperation between the US, Canada, and Mexico in addressing the challenge. There is also mention of the "Buy American" provisions, the drug cartels in Mexico, and the Merida Initiative. The briefing concludes with a Q&A session.